They do. The intake fails because of a design  flaw.




hey Richard  Not really a design flaw.  What happens is that the  intake air 
is cooler than the combustion chamber and the seats on the intake  don't 
expand as much as the head itself is and then they come loose. As you said  can be 
controlled by a CHT gage and not letting the heads get too  hot.   later  mark 
